00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:49,210
the cost and to organize
the tariff collection.

164
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:55,050
The cost of the service must be
financed by tariff collection

165
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:56,930
or by other municipal resources.

166
00:12:57,770 --> 00:13:02,000
This is the first political decision
to decide which part should

167
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:06,280
be covered by tariffs and which
part by other resources.

168
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:11,990
There are four basic recovery
principles for tariff setting.

169
00:13:12,970 --> 00:13:19,010
The first principle is a polluter
pays system: the waste generator

170
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:21,180
has to pay for its elimination.

171
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:26,860
Second point is the transparency:
tariffs should reflect

172
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:31,250
the cost and the citizens should be
informed in a transparent way

173
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:33,660
on the cost and tariff calculation.

174
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:39,800
Thirdly, the cost recovery
principle: the amount of collected

175
00:13:39,830 --> 00:13:46,180
tariffs should be close to the
expenses – not under, not over.

176
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:51,770
Finally, the simplicity of the tax
calculation and the tax recovery

177
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:53,280
system is very important.

178
00:13:55,100 --> 00:14:00,270
Tax system should be based on the
available data and it is very

179
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:03,160
important that the system
is simple to operate.

180
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:08,980
We will not enter in the definition
of each possible system

181
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:13,910
