consider some basic questions.

182
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:17,850
First question is: which part
of the cost should be covered

183
00:14:18,110 --> 00:14:19,860
by taxes or by other resources?

184
00:14:21,410 --> 00:14:25,370
Also, which part of the cost
should be covered by businesses

185
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:31,580
or by families or inhabitants?
Also, should all the citizens

186
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:35,760
pay the same tax, or should the
tax be adapted following

187
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:39,690
the equality of services, the zone
of the city, the frequency of

188
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:41,810
the service, the distances
of the service?

189
00:14:43,190 --> 00:14:46,270
Other important question is:
how to calculate the tax?

190
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:51,250
Per inhabitant or per family, or
per bin or per square meter

191
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:56,500
of the main house, or in proportion
of electricity or water use?

192
00:14:56,500 --> 00:15:01,500
Other question is: how to
establish an update?

193
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:04,730
On the clients and billing data basis?

194
00:15:05,990 --> 00:15:07,460
How to collect the taxes?

195
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:12,090
Alone or together as a service
like electricity or water?

196
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:17,440
Other question is: how to inform
the population about the taxes

197
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:20,600
and about the importance
to pay the taxes?

198
00:15:22,190 --> 00:15:25,020
Other question is: how to
react when people don't pay?

199
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:29,060
How to integer the poorest
people in the system?

